The coastal provinces of the country can expect cool weather conditions, while the central interior will be cold to very cold, according to the South African Weather Service. The weather in your region Gauteng will be fine and warm. The expected UVB sunburn index will be very high. It will be fine and warm but very hot in places in the Lowveld of Mpumalanga. Limpopo will be fine and warm but hot in the Lowveld and Limpopo Valley. It will be fine and warm in the North West. The Free State will be fine and cool to warm. The Northern Cape will be partly cloudy and cold with morning fog patches over the southern interior. Otherwise, it will fine and warm and cool. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh southerly to south-easterly. It will be cloudy in the south west in the Western Cape with isolated showers. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool to cold. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh westerly to south-westerly. The expected UVB sunburn index will be moderate The Eastern Cape is expected to be fine and warm. The wind along the coast will be moderate. There will be morning fog along the escarpment of KwaZulu-Natal. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool but fine in the west. It will become cloudy along the coast and adjacent interior with isolated showers and rain. The wind along the coast will be moderate south-westerly becoming south-easterly by late afternoon. The expected UVB sunburn index will be high.  Click here to see the specific forecast for your city over the next few days GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 